          <declname>safe_threshold</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initialize the boot manager. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Loads boot data from flash, increments boot counter, checks for crash loops. Call this very early in boot.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>boot</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Boot manager instance. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>store</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Initialized parameter store for boot data. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>safe_threshold</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of consecutive failed boots before safe mode. Set to 0 to disable safe mode detection. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>SYN_OK on normal boot, SYN_ERROR on first-ever boot (no data). </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
